        <div class="forum_topic_posts_info_body">
          Japanese woman from Sierra Leone hospitalized over Ebola infection fears<br />
JIJI<br />
JAN 18, 2015<br />
ARTICLE HISTORY<br />
PRINT SHARE<br />
A Japanese woman in her 70s who returned from Sierra Leone last week has been taken to the National Center for Global Health and Medicine hospital after fears she might be infected with the deadly Ebola virus, government officials said Sunday.<br />
<br />
After arriving in Japan on Tuesday from the West African nation for a temporary homecoming, she saw her body temperature rise beyond 38 degrees Celsius on Sunday afternoon, the officials said.<br />
<br />
A sample of her blood will be sent to the National Institute of Infectious Diseases to check for Ebola.<br />
<br />
Apparently, the woman did not come into direct contact with any Ebola patients during her stay in Sierra Leone, the officials said.                  </div>
                  <div class="forum_topic_posts_info_photo">
